# Home Media Server Environment Configuration

# Storage Configuration
# Customize these paths to match your storage setup

# Root path for media files (movies, TV shows, music)
# Default: /mnt/WD_1T/media
MEDIA_ROOT=/mnt/WD_1T/media

# Root path for downloads
# Default: /mnt/WD_1T/downloads  
DOWNLOADS_ROOT=/mnt/WD_1T/downloads

# Examples for different setups:

# For macOS users:
# MEDIA_ROOT=/Volumes/External Drive/media
# DOWNLOADS_ROOT=/Volumes/External Drive/downloads

# For Windows users with WSL:
# MEDIA_ROOT=/mnt/d/media
# DOWNLOADS_ROOT=/mnt/d/downloads

# For different Linux mount points:
# MEDIA_ROOT=/media/storage/media
# DOWNLOADS_ROOT=/media/storage/downloads

# For NAS storage:
# MEDIA_ROOT=/mnt/nas/media
# DOWNLOADS_ROOT=/mnt/nas/downloads

# Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file to .env (remove .example)
# 2. Modify the paths above to match your storage
# 3. Ensure the directories exist and have proper permissions:
#    mkdir -p $MEDIA_ROOT/{tv,movies,music}
#    mkdir -p $DOWNLOADS_ROOT
# 4. Start the containers: docker-compose up -d
